{%- comment -%}
  main-about.liquid — body content for the About page.
  Edit this file to update the page. No section editor in admin.
  SEO + JSON-LD live in snippets/seo-meta.liquid (context-aware via page.handle).
{%- endcomment -%}

<header class="hero short">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> About · Two founders · Operator-led</span>
      <h1>We're operators first.<br/><em>Consultants by accident.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">Lighter Fluid was founded in 2024 as a generalist studio. By 2026, the work that mattered most was the AI operating systems we'd been building for our own businesses — and for the enterprise clients one of us had been advising for years before that. So that's what we sell now.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>This site, our process, and the framework library all came from the same place: trying to run three businesses with the systems available in 2024 and finding them inadequate. The skills we build for clients are the skills we built for ourselves first. The standards documents we install are the standards we wrote for our own teams.</p>

        <p>That's the only honest claim we can make in 2026. We don't have a long client roster yet. We have three businesses we built, the operating playbook those businesses run on, and a strong opinion that this playbook compounds when other operators install it.</p>

        <p class="pullquote">
          We sound like operators describing what they actually built. Not consultants pitching what they could.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FOUNDERS ============ -->
  <section class="section sm rule">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">The founders</span>
        <h2>Two operators.<br/><em>Different specialties.<br/>Same shop.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="founder-cards">
        <article class="founder-card">
          <header>
            <img class="avatar" src="{{ 'founder-gabe.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Gabe Coyne" width="56" height="56">
            <div class="ident">
              <h3>Gabe Coyne</h3>
              <p class="role">Founder · Visionary</p>
            </div>
          </header>
          <ul class="credit-list">
            <li><span class="num">$200M+</span><span class="line">Co-founded Influence Mobile · #3 mobile ad network in the world · 100M+ installs delivered</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">$100M+</span><span class="line">Co-founded Stix Golf in 2020 · $8M year one · Series A &amp; B</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">$4.5M</span><span class="line">CEO of Host Modern · year one · 10%+ profit margin</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">10 yrs</span><span class="line">Creative-services studio in Seattle (pre-Influence Mobile)</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">Partner</span><span class="line">Prota Ventures · innovation consulting for Exelon, ADP, Citi Bank</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="bio">The Prota work was the prototype for what Lighter Fluid does now: take a client's idea through design, prototype, validation, launch, and scale — and document the system enough that the client team can keep running it.</p>
          <p class="bio">Mobile-ad-network background is where the technical instincts come from (attribution under noise, real-time decisioning, fraud detection). DTC is the operating playbook. Prota is the consulting discipline.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <a class="card-link" href="mailto:gabe@lighterfluid.co">Email →</a>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gabecoyne" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn →</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="founder-card">
          <header>
            <img class="avatar" src="{{ 'founder-collin.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Collin Duff" width="56" height="56">
            <div class="ident">
              <h3>Collin Duff</h3>
              <p class="role">Co-Founder · Integrator</p>
            </div>
          </header>
          <ul class="credit-list">
            <li><span class="num">COO</span><span class="line">Host Modern · through its launch</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">Head of Product</span><span class="line">Stix Golf · current</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">Co-founder</span><span class="line">Viator Coffee</span></li>
            <li><span class="num">Operator</span><span class="line">Product-and-ops counterweight to Gabe's growth-and-systems instinct</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="bio">Owns the work that doesn't fit cleanly in a skill — the new product evaluation framework at Stix, the SEO landing page program at Host Modern, the Shopify autopilot loop that auto-deploys low-risk fixes from a Slack channel.</p>
          <p class="bio">If a client engagement involves shipping product or fixing a stack-deep operational gap, Collin runs it.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <a class="card-link" href="mailto:collin@lighterfluid.co">Email →</a>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/collin-duff-1bba92144/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn →</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- ============ BETWEEN US (charcoal) ============ -->
  <section class="section dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">Between us</span>
        <h2>What two operators<br/><em>have put on the board.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="big-stat-grid">
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">5</div>
          <div class="label">Businesses launched</div>
          <div class="desc">Stix, Host Modern, Influence Mobile, Viator Coffee, creative studio.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">$300M+</div>
          <div class="label">Lifetime revenue</div>
          <div class="desc">Across all five businesses we have operated.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">$50M+</div>
          <div class="label">Capital raised</div>
          <div class="desc">Across Series A, Series B, and earlier rounds.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">100K+</div>
          <div class="label">Customers</div>
          <div class="desc">Hundreds of thousands across the brands.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">100s</div>
          <div class="label">Employees hired</div>
          <div class="desc">Operators recruited, onboarded, managed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">100s</div>
          <div class="label">Products to market</div>
          <div class="desc">Concept through launch — digital and physical.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">1,000s</div>
          <div class="label">SKUs managed</div>
          <div class="desc">Across product lines, seasons, channels.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="big-stat">
          <div class="val">Forbes</div>
          <div class="label">Awards &amp; press</div>
          <div class="desc">Sports Illustrated, Entrepreneur, Golf Magazine, MoMA, Mission.org.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ HOW WE WORK ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">How we work</span>
        <h2>A partnership.<br/><em>Not an agency.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="tile-grid">
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">01 · Two principals</span>
          <h3>Both founders, every engagement.</h3>
          <p>No account manager layer. No junior swap-in after kickoff. You get the people whose names are on the door.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">02 · Builder = explainer</span>
          <h3>The person who ships is the person who teaches.</h3>
          <p>The hand that wires the skill is the hand that walks your team through it. The person who scopes is the person who presents.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">03 · Capped capacity</span>
          <h3>Four active engagements.<br/>Maximum.</h3>
          <p>We won't take on more than the two of us can run honestly. Caps how many we say yes to. We say no a lot.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">04 · Small by design</span>
          <h3>This caps the company we're building.</h3>
          <p>Caps the engagements. Caps the headcount. Caps the revenue ceiling. We're fine with all three.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT WE BELIEVE ============ -->
  <section class="section sm">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">What we believe</span>
        <h2>Four positions.<br/><em>Held under load.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="tile-grid">
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">Position 01</span>
          <h3>Operators understand operators.</h3>
          <p>Most consulting fails because the consultant never lived with the recommendation. Every framework in our library exists because we hit the wall it solves.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">Position 02</span>
          <h3>Standards beat strategy.</h3>
          <p>Strategy decks compound badly. Standards documents compound well. Every framework we install is one your team can extend without us. That's the whole product.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">Position 03</span>
          <h3>Speed without panic.</h3>
          <p>AI lets you ship faster. It also lets you ship faster in the wrong direction. The frameworks keep speed and rigor compatible — so you don't burn budget on bad signal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <span class="num">Position 04</span>
          <h3>Documented or it didn't ship.</h3>
          <p>A skill that runs but isn't documented breaks the day a model deprecates. We treat documentation as half the deliverable. We charge accordingly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT WE WILL / WON'T DO ============ -->
  <section class="section sm">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">The deal</span>
        <h2>What we will.<br/><em>What we won't.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="yesno">
        <div class="col yes">
          <h3>We will</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Bring two principals to every engagement.</li>
            <li>Cap the work at four active engagements at once.</li>
            <li>Refer you to a better consultancy if we're not the fit.</li>
            <li>Tell you the first call is free, and mean it.</li>
            <li>Hand you documentation that outlives us.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col no">
          <h3>We won't</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Hire a junior team to scale past our cap.</li>
            <li>Sell you hours.</li>
            <li>Write the deck and disappear.</li>
            <li>Pitch industries where operator credibility doesn't transfer.</li>
            <li>Take engagements that compromise the partnership cap.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:32px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--lf-ink-soft);max-width:680px;text-wrap:pretty;">If those constraints fit your need, the first call is free. If they don't, we'll refer you to a consultancy that fits better — the AI consulting market is bigger than us.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-block dark">
        <h2>Two operators.<br/><em>Two weeks.</em><br/>One deck you can use whether you hire us or not.</h2>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn ember" href="{{ routes.root_url }}pages/contact">Book a call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

